    "title": "Property Consultant - CBRE India - Multiple Openings",
    "description": "Are you a skilled Property Consultant looking for your next big career move? CBRE India in Chandigarh offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout CBRE India:\nCBRE India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage relationships with existing customers post-purchase\n• Maintain a pipeline of qualified leads using CRM software\n• Negotiate pricing, terms, and conditions on behalf of clients\n• Achieve monthly and quarterly sales targets\n• Provide advisory services on property investment and market trends\n• Conduct land acquisition due diligence and feasibility studies\n• Manage RERA documentation and compliance requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Client Relationship Management\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in Contract Management\n• Proficiency in MS Office\n• Proficiency in Market Research\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in GIS Tools\n• Proficiency in Property Valuation\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Learning & development budget\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chandigarh, Punjab, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with CBRE India!",
